  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nImplement network selection dropdown UI in \r\n- Wallet Home\r\n- Account screen.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"565\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19339952/2099cf77-fa0a-4eab-b2c0-c0a821cd3ac8\">\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\nWallet home: [Figma Link](https://www.figma.com/file/HKncH4wnDwZDAhc4AryK8Y/Wallet-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=1%3A46865&mode=design&t=H2vraH5nSHXL10D8-1)\r\n\r\nAccounts: [Figma Link](https://www.figma.com/file/HKncH4wnDwZDAhc4AryK8Y/Wallet-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=7559%3A197421&mode=design&t=H2vraH5nSHXL10D8-1)\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn Wallet Home, on tap of the networks (next to the aggregated balance display), the dropdown with networks checkboxes will be shown.\r\n\r\nOn the Account page, on the tap of networks (in the navigation bar), the dropdown with networks checkboxes will be shown.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n - Network dropdown is shown on tap of the networks on Wallet Home and Account page\r\n - The component should be reusable on both screens and should be placed in `status-im.contexts.wallet.common.sheets.*` ns\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- Display `0.00` on each network as this issue deals with only implementing and placing the UI in place. \r\n- The filtering of tokens will be handled in a separate issue\r\n",
